    <ThingDef ParentName="HP_AoD_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>GW_SM_FibroVest</defName>
        <label>fibrovest</label>
        <description>A specially-designed vest worn under Power Armor. Its systems interface with the users nervous system and link it to the Power Armors artificial muscles, allowing them to move the armor as if it was their own body.\n\nIn the Age of the Imperium, this role used to be played by the Black Carapace implant, which looked like a layer of black plastic under the skin. This implant linked the Marines nervous system to their Power Armor, allowing them to control it - additionally, it also linked the user to their vehicles, giving them a greater degree of control. However, the Space Marine creation process has been lost to time, forcing the Imperiums remnants to improvise.</description>
        <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>GW_SM_AstartesFabrication</researchPrerequisite>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/OnSkin/FibroLayer/FibroLayer_Male_south</texPath>
        </graphicData>
        <apparel>
            <wornGraphicPath>Things/OnSkin/FibroLayer/FibroLayer</wornGraphicPath>
            <tags>
                <li>GW_SM_FibroVest</li>
            </tags>
        </apparel>
    </ThingDef>
</Defs>
